SIMPLE: spirituous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spirituous
<hw>Spir"it*u*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. (for sense
2) F. <ets>spiritueux</ets>. Cf. <er>Spiritous</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having the quality of spirit; tenuous in substance, and having
active powers or properties; ethereal; immaterial; spiritual;
pure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Containing, or of the nature of, alcoholic (esp.
distilled) spirit; consisting of refined spirit; alcoholic; ardent;
<as>as, <ex>spirituous</ex> liquors</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Lively; gay; vivid; airy.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir H. Wotton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mind of man is of that <qex>spirituous</qex>, stirring nature,
that it is perpetually at work.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spirituousness</ent>⟦br⟧
